    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT PAVE BANK\n\nPave Bank is the world’s first programmable business bank. Built by the founders behind Monzo and BigPay, we’re redefining global business banking by combining programmable financial infrastructure with world-class client experiences.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe are looking for a highly experienced Mobile Engineer (React Native) to own the development of our cross-platform banking application end-to-end. You will have the autonomy to make key technical decisions, define best practices, and set the standard for frontend development, testing, and deployment.\n\nThis role is ideal for someone who thrives on ownership, enjoys architecting products, and wants to make a lasting impact on both the product and engineering culture.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Architect and build a mobile banking application using React Native with TypeScript\n\n - Deliver high‑quality, responsive, and performant UI/UX in collaboration with designers and product owners\n\n - Integrate with backend services and third‑party APIs securely and reliably\n\n - Set up and maintain CI/CD pipelines for automated builds, testing, and deployments\n\n - Set standards for code quality, performance, security, and maintainability\n\n - Define and execute a strong mobile testing strategy (unit, integration, and end‑to‑end tests)\n\n - Champion code quality through clean code, reviews, documentation, and best practices\n\n - Monitor, measure, and improve app performance, stability, and scalability\n\n - Partner with cross‑functional teams (design, backend, QA, product) to ship features end‑to‑end\n\n - Continuously identify opportunities to improve development processes and tools\n\n\nWHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - Proven experience building production-grade mobile applications from scratch\n\n - Expert in React Native + TypeScript, with deep frontend knowledge\n\n - Strong understanding of mobile performance, security, and UX best practices\n\n - Comfortable making technical decisions and driving standards\n\n - Experience setting up CI/CD pipelines and automated testing workflows\n\n - Independent, proactive, and able to thrive in a startup environment\n\n - Passionate about fintech, security, and building scalable products\n\n - Minimum 5 years of mobile development experience, ideally with full lifecycle experience from scratch to production\n\n - Experience as a founding or early mobile engineer at a fintech or high-growth startup is a strong plus\n\n - Familiarity with cross-platform challenges and optimizing for both iOS and Android\n\n\nWHY US?\n\n - We recently raised $39 million in our Series A (led by Accel), positioning the company for major growth and giving you a rare chance to join while things are still moving fast\n\n - We're building a fully-licensed programmable bank, rearchitecting how money moves between businesses, across borders, and between traditional and digital finance\n\n - We ship fast, think deeply, and expect everyone to have high ownership\n\n - Work with engineers who were founding engineers at Monzo, Atom Bank, and Blockdaemon",
